The mesoporous WO3–TiO2 composite thin films coated on ITO substrate and annealed at 450, 500, and 600 °C were immersed in an ethanolic solution of ruthenium dye [(cis-bis (isothiocyanato) bis (2,2’ bipyridyl-4,4’ dicarboxylato) ruthenium (II)] to obtain dye sensitized WO3–TiO2 layers. These dye sensitized WO3–TiO2 layers were used as active electrodes for the construction of photochromic (PE) devices. Then, the ion conducting (IC) solution containing a redox couple (I− and I3−) and Li ions was spread over the dye sensitized WO3–TiO2 composite layer. Several PE systems were constructed with the following configuration:ITO-coatedglass1/WO3-TiO2-Ru(II)-dye/ICLayer(ICL)/ITO-coatedglass2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
